Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.72,0:00:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the middle of winter, at the South Pole, yowls a withering\Nwind, blowing faster than 50 meters per second.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.35,0:00:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A true world of shadow, where for\Nmonths the sun never shines.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.19,0:00:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The temperature reaches minus 60 °C.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.74,0:00:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the frosted surface, in the middle of winter,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.66,0:00:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stands deadpan and silent a flock of shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.62,0:00:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emperor penguins, of the penguin species, penguin family,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.46,0:00:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,scientific name: {\i1}Aptenodytes forsteri{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.21,0:00:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The female of this species, which is the largest of its kind,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.88,0:00:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,lays its eggs at the very climax of the\Npolar winter, between June and July.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.56,0:00:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, in order to provide food,\Nshe migrates to far away seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.77,0:00:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly at that moment begins the\Npenguin father's incubation hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.75,0:01:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However icy the wind may be be,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.92,0:01:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he grabs the egg with his feet, and\Ncovers it with his ponderous body.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.76,0:01:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For his beloved egg, it doesn't matter how\Nsad and painful his suffering may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.47,0:01:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a honorable man, he puts that suffering aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.10,0:01:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,summons his strrrrrong spirit, and guts it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.69,0:01:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.49,0:01:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He awaits, without drinking or eating,\Nthe birth of the little one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.95,0:01:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows how much and how badly\Nthis father penguin suffers,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.62,0:01:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who incubates at all cost in the hard frost and darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.42,0:01:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everywhere the eye can see, the wind\Nblows over the frozen plains,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:02:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,without even the shadow of a bar to drink\Nin, or a small warm soba place to eat in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.64,0:02:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His thoughts are always addressed to the\Nday when the mother penguin will return,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.55,0:02:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's nothing he can do about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.43,0:02:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a poor family needs a good wife like an unstable\Ngovernment needs a good president.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.31,0:02:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that he can't even aspire to something\Nlike the smell of his wife's homemade stew...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.40,0:02:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that in the end, all he can do\Nis sigh, far away from his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.49,0:02:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During the hard time of gestation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.03,0:02:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and for at least the six weeks that it takes following the\Nhatching for the little ones to learn to walk on the ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.29,0:02:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we know that the father penguin\Nloses as much as 10 cm of fat,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.46,0:02:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that his weight is cut in half!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.18,0:02:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All parents think about their sons, and cry when doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The father emperor penguin sheds\Nmany tears for his little one,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.10,0:02:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and this was the story of his great patience!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.75,0:03:22.26,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,I watch the sky through the keyhole, and\Nwhat I see is a person's silhouette
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.92,0:03:28.72,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my casual encounter with a tomorrow I've never seen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.14,0:03:34.56,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Outer space always starts from an interphone
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.35,0:03:41.11,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, one step out, and I find the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.48,0:03:47.16,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no armor to protect the family
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.70,0:03:54.41,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,The only weapon to search for our roots is consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:04:04.26,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,If only you had love, dreams, and frontiers...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.26,0:04:16.06,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Lineage, the road home, heritage, and\Norigins depend on space and time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.60,0:04:24.40,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,The wife has the household, the servant, and the genealogy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.57,0:04:29.45,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Transcend and run through the time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.41,0:04:35.75,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,Long long life to the ancestors!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.40,0:05:50.40,title1,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinekuni Yomota
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.40,0:05:50.40,title2,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru\NMaroko\NDog
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.24,0:05:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The airship of that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.01,0:06:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather! How is the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.30,0:06:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.81,0:06:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.35,0:06:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.77,0:06:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ко!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.39,0:06:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you come too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.98,0:06:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.52,0:06:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come rub your grandpa's back! All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.19,0:06:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... I'd be embarrassed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.95,0:06:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's embarrassing about taking a bath with your grandpa?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.37,0:06:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come, I'll close my eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.71,0:06:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.45,0:07:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You piece of...! Do you think you're funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.33,0:07:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you find funny in this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.80,0:08:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Fantastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.01,0:08:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Daddy! What a marvelous stew!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.30,0:08:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.55,0:08:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Great-Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.51,0:08:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.47,0:08:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather Inumaru, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.85,0:08:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning to you, Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.44,0:08:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It really looks delicious, now doesn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.11,0:08:33.65,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Nabe-style means a dish cooked in broth in one pot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.11,0:08:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko sure loves nabe-style cooking! If\NI'm right, yesterday's dinner was also...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.65,0:08:35.82,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Ishikari-nabe is made with salmon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.65,0:08:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ishikari-nabe! And for lunch, sukiyaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.82,0:08:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the day before...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.61,0:08:40.16,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Tecchiri is nabe made with blowfish (fugu);\Nyanagawa is nabe made with loach.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.61,0:08:40.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For lunch tecchiri, for dinner yanagawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.16,0:08:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the day before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.49,0:08:43.45,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Mizore nabe is made with grated daikon (white radishes).
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.49,0:08:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Codfish nabe with boiled tofu and mizore nabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.45,0:08:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's always been my wish to see all the family around a nabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.04,0:08:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Together with my grandfather and great-grandfather,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.58,0:08:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while we eat warm dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.71,0:08:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A moment of family union, where\NI could tell you about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.84,0:08:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Family equals nabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.76,0:09:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for the meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.48,0:09:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since Maroko suddenly came to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.40,0:09:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since that Sunday of ennui, well, ten days have passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.61,0:09:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It shouldn't be for me, the great-grandpa, to say so, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.66,0:09:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.46,0:09:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she's really a well-made young girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.79,0:09:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I go out in the morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.67,0:09:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a nice day, Great-Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.17,0:09:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when I come back, tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back home, Great-Grandfather.\NYou worked hard today, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.34,0:09:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She not only does all the washing and prepares the\Nmeals, but she also rubs my back in the bath,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.56,0:09:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a way of welcoming no less than perfect,\Nnot to mention all of the shadow work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.19,0:09:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, {\i1}that{\i0} smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.02,0:09:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her marvelous smile that, when you're tired,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.73,0:09:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,gives you the courage to protect this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.95,0:10:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sure don't want to play the role of the master\Nwho only wants to be served and revered.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the master of the house, given that there\Nis someone able to build a base of trust...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.00,0:10:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this drama, I get the strength to play the\Nrole of a hard-fighting family master!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.88,0:10:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.96,0:10:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.76,0:10:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've changed from what I've been up to now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.26,0:10:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very motivated. I wish to sustain this family, for Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.05,0:10:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my days are full of real meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.81,0:10:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to our encounter with Maroko,\Nwho has become part of our family,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I myself have changed my role into none other\Nthan that of real family leader and father!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.19,0:10:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I could never part from Maroko,\Nwhatever her true nature might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.12,0:10:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I decided to come live in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.45,0:10:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accepted Maroko's wish to live only with\Nthe family, without any strangers around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.58,0:10:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, to display a family\Nin its best and most fitting form.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.54,0:10:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for me, a man no longer young,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.30,0:11:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who doesn't even know if he can pay back the\Nmortgage, I've now become more human.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.26,0:11:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has truly been a very risky decision, but\Nat present I no longer fear anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.18,0:11:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To tell the truth, there is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.81,0:11:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if my son Inumaru, forgetting about\Nhis role as Maroko's ancestor,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.02,0:11:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or even worse, exploiting this role,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.11,0:11:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,starts to outfox Maroko with his babbling\Nchatter! That's my only fear...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.82,0:11:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.16,0:11:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried about my wife Tamiko, who left because\Nof the fuss when Maroko entered our household.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.20,0:11:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a very proud woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.91,0:11:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no sign of her, even at her relatives' houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.17,0:11:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows where she is, and what she's doing...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a rule that time travellers must\Nnever break, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.83,0:12:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Specifically, they must never interact with\Nthe past in a way that alters the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.08,0:12:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We call this the "Principle of Historical Non-Intervention"...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.67,0:12:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.05,0:12:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.05,0:12:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the middle of the 21st century,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.47,0:12:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,people have appeared, one after another,\Nwho use the time machine at will,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.64,0:12:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and who, ignoring the law, get in\Ntouch with their own ancestors,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.47,0:12:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,entering into improper personal relations with their relatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.14,0:13:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such an illegal interaction upsets genealogy,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.39,0:13:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and fuels societal instability.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.65,0:13:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For this reason, the government,\Nthrough the Ministry of Health,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.44,0:13:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has created the Agency for Time Administration,\Nand among its members
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.69,0:13:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are staff who act severely against time-related mischiefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.03,0:13:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Agency for Time Administration in the Ministry of Health
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.66,0:13:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,counters these criminal groups\Nthrough an investigative group.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.41,0:13:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This investigative group is known as "The\NGuard Dogs of Time"... the Time Patrol!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.42,0:13:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In our work as defenders of history,\Nsupporting the temporal flow,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.96,0:13:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's no such word as "tomorrow"!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.06,0:13:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Muruto Bunmei.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.47,0:13:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Special Department for Anti-Historical Crime, responsible\Nfor the surveillance of the end of the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.48,0:13:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,38 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.86,0:13:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Single.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.07,0:13:50.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yomota Maroko! For the crimes of\Nimproper use of a time machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.61,0:13:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and improper relations with your relatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.65,0:13:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I declare you under arrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.05,0:14:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.01,0:14:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Note: Sticking chopsticks into food is a very disrespectful act.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.05,0:14:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been listening to all of your babble.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.35,0:14:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you enter so shamelessly\Ninto other people's family drama?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.27,0:14:23.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you, brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.73,0:14:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.40,0:14:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.73,0:14:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Muruto Bunmei!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Special Department for Anti-Historical Crime, responsible\Nfor the surveillance of the end of the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.36,0:14:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,38 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.57,0:14:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understood that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.49,0:14:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yomota Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.08,0:14:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the crimes of improper use of a time machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.45,0:14:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already understood that too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.04,0:14:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, in that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.12,0:14:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait already!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.88,0:14:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.13,0:14:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we wanted to check whether\Nyou really came from near future,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.97,0:15:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we could never be sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.76,0:15:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've already accepted the incredible story that this\Ngirl came from the future and is your granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.40,0:15:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you don't have the guts to reject that story,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.82,0:15:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you sure as hell can't reject my version either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.53,0:15:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.07,0:15:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, even admitting that you're\Nreally from the Time Patrol...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.08,0:15:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.37,0:15:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what mischief has Maroko done to merit arrest?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.75,0:15:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.75,0:15:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.79,0:15:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.96,0:15:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.50,0:15:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you what's this stuff boiling on\Nthe burner and looking so damn delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.55,0:15:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I'm asking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.18,0:15:40.59,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Yose-nabe is made with seafood and chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.18,0:15:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a simple yose-nabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.10,0:15:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First thing in the morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether we eat it for breakfast, lunch, or\Ndinner is none of your fucking business!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.60,0:15:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is your problem with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.94,0:15:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know who decided, and why, where, and when,\Nthat eating yose-nabe first thing in the morning is a crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.02,0:15:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a violation of the law?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.69,0:15:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do people get arrested for it? Or put to death?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.91,0:15:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.16,0:16:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,eating yose-nabe or sukiyaki first thing in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.29,0:16:08.25,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Chankonabe is a protein-rich nabe eaten by sumo wrestlers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.29,0:16:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or vegetable stew, or chankonabe...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.25,0:16:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody can charge you with a crime for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.34,0:16:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,HOWEVER!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.34,0:16:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A blood relative who shouldn't even be here,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.47,0:16:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in other words, a great-granddaughter who comes\Nfrom the near future in a time machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.89,0:16:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,absolutely can't eat and live with her ancestors!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.73,0:16:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to article 538, subsection 8,\Nof the Code of Time Administration,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.23,0:16:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's forbidden to enter into improper\Nrelations with one's own ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.36,0:16:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time travellers are forbidden to get in touch\Nvoluntarily with people of the same blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.66,0:16:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.58,0:16:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just wrong to go meet your ancestors\Nwhenever you feel like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.16,0:16:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And as if it wasn't enough, to live with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.37,0:16:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to cook stew first thing in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.17,0:16:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to play the happy-family role!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.80,0:16:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.09,0:17:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true, she's a great-granddaughter come from the future,\Nbut this doesn't change the fact that she's part of the family!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.80,0:17:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong in doing a stew for the family?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.97,0:17:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it bother someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.44,0:17:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does someone die?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.73,0:17:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does someone get pissed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.94,0:17:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do get pissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.94,0:17:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And why the hell do you get pissed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.31,0:17:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get pissed because it violates the law!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.98,0:17:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you get pissed if the law is violated?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.61,0:17:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.36,0:17:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what do {\i1}you{\i0} mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.49,0:17:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.36,0:17:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really understand your feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.58,0:17:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who wouldn't love his own granddaughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.50,0:17:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's sweet, she's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.25,0:17:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And moreover, she's a beautiful, obedient\Ngirl, who manages every kind of task.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.71,0:17:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A good-for-nothing bum of a son; an idiot\Ngirl who has nothing to do with him;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.55,0:17:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a loser of a father who only thinks\Nabout being served and revered;
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.31,0:17:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in our peaceful Japan, a family at the end of the\Ncentury finds itself in the middle of a conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.27,0:17:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if the ideal of the family, the mirror of relationships,\Nis realized through the arrival of this girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.65,0:18:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if she starts to live with her glorious\Nancestors, how would the world end?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.58,0:18:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will never part from Maroko!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.21,0:18:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I lost Maroko, what else would sustain my existence?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.38,0:18:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After my wife Tamiko left me, all I have is that bum Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.68,0:18:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you! Do you have the slightest idea\Nhow much you've upset this family?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.14,0:18:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not Maroko's fault at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.73,0:18:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom left of her own free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.52,0:18:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Mom who's in the wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.36,0:18:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that's the proper way to speak\Nabout the person who gave you life?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.32,0:18:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.78,0:18:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How I speak about my parents is none of your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.61,0:18:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surely not going to listen to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.16,0:18:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! This guy is threatening to take Maroko away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.75,0:18:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.21,0:18:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at your son, your real son... Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.84,0:19:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has already started to spit poison!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.88,0:19:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of this girl, your wife has left, and your\Nson is becoming an unrecoverable case!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.64,0:19:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since she arrived, this family has started going to pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.64,0:19:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was hopeless from the beginning.\NIt's as if I hadn't said anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.56,0:19:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all the fault of this societal garbage!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.31,0:19:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.02,0:19:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What right do you have to come into\Nmy house, and get mad at my son,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.57,0:19:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and shoot your "idiot" and "societal garbage" everywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.07,0:19:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.24,0:19:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter whether your brat is\Na piece of shit, a son is always a son,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.53,0:19:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if he's attacked by a stranger, it gets on your nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.95,0:19:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"No... My son is not that type of person..."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.42,0:19:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the problem of blood relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.50,0:19:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the limit of blood relationships, do you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.38,0:19:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.01,0:19:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.51,0:19:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I called your father an old good-for-nothing\Nfart, you'd get pissed too, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.01,0:19:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.35,0:19:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The problem has resulted from one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.19,0:20:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the first half of the 21st century,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.48,0:20:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,perhaps in reaction to the tendency\Nof families to break down easily,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.49,0:20:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a growing respect toward the ancestors\Nhas begun to manifest itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.86,0:20:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,showing as veneration of them and of\Nthe family more than anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.04,0:20:19.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A time machine has been created that\Nannihilates the chasm of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.46,0:20:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the number of people who travel through\Ntime has grown astronomically,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.46,0:20:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,each hoping to meet their ancestors at least once.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.13,0:20:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's become a real social phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.05,0:20:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And isn't it just great?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.89,0:20:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.26,0:20:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now my great-grandfather said...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.89,0:20:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that he would never part from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.23,0:20:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel the same! I'd like to stay by my grandfathers'\Nside and assist them in everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.69,0:20:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to do everything in my power for the\Nprosperity and the happiness of this family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.91,0:20:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.41,0:20:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was a dangerous idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.12,0:21:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This turned out to be the trigger for anti-social ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.63,0:21:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Time travellers can do anything that they can think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.55,0:21:11.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can protect people who would otherwise\Nhave died from sickness or accidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.72,0:21:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can assure, through their knowledge of\Nthe future, the social success of this society.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.43,0:21:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Families can become happy, and in the\Nfuture, everything can be for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.48,0:21:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what if everyone starts doing this? What\Nkind of mess would history become?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.03,0:21:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the future? And the country?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.32,0:21:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.07,0:21:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the future? What is the country?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.45,0:21:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does my family have to be the victim of all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.29,0:21:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you want to take away my family's happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.12,0:21:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's egotistical to think only of your own\Nfamily's welfare and happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.51,0:21:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dimension free from temporal bounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.60,0:21:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a world in which solidarity overcomes temporal bounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.52,0:22:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an existence that overcomes by far the concept of family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.36,0:22:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The birth of a new country.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.19,0:22:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.03,0:22:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't disturb us at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.36,0:22:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make it so simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.95,0:22:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The country doesn't want another country inside itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.83,0:22:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the country bases its position only upon itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.34,0:22:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and has as an essential condition\Nits unique and singular existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.97,0:22:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The family only establishes a basis for the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.84,0:22:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and is nothing more than a group of people who\Nserve to perpetuate the basis of the country!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.85,0:22:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot forgive the unfaithful individuals\Nwho want to overcome this limit!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.23,0:22:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drink it! Drink it! Drink it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.88,0:23:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, you've revealed your true nature, you damn old fart!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.60,0:23:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was "Protect history, protect\Nthe future from the past," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.81,0:23:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just all talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.85,0:23:30.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, you're not a guard dog of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.02,0:23:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but just a small mutt under the yoke\Nof the temporal authorities!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.65,0:23:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I'm an agent!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.28,0:23:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.07,0:23:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you think that I'd leave Maroko\Nin the hands of a bastard like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.21,0:23:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Grandfather! Bunmei is an awful man!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.09,0:23:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moron. Do you want to die so badly?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.40,0:24:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong now, brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.28,0:24:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, a UFO...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.86,0:24:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Where? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.72,0:24:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.68,0:24:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what do we do with him now?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.81,0:24:48.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.23,0:24:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.64,0:24:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.44,0:24:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.06,0:24:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel terrible that you'll be living here alone, from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.07,0:25:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you understand me, don't you, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.57,0:25:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.53,0:25:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no other solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.20,0:25:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we defeated that one...\Nanother will certainly come.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.25,0:25:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since our family has now made this small mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.75,0:25:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we can't stay here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.29,0:25:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.50,0:25:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.38,0:25:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready, Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.92,0:25:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were leaving this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.13,0:25:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.01,0:25:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I beat up a Time Patrol\Nagent, I'm also party to a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.93,0:25:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice but to run away together!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.73,0:25:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Great-Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.81,0:25:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The three of us would be too visible,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.98,0:25:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and in his injured condition,\Nhe certainly can't live as a fugitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.61,0:25:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's painful, we have to part.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.69,0:25:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The die is cast! We have no alternative!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.45,0:25:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, then... Grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.08,0:25:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! The savings account and the stamps are in the drawer!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.25,0:25:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And don't forget the credit card!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.34,0:26:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Dad, what beautiful weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.59,0:26:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ideal weather for a young couple\Nto run away from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.14,0:26:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.56,0:26:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.40,0:26:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right... I've been waiting for this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.74,0:26:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the day she appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.36,0:26:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the end of this pathetic drama!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.99,0:26:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A life as fugitives, full of danger, together with Maroko.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.87,0:26:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A world in which the passion between two\Nyoung people sparks from day to day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.42,0:26:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what I've always wanted!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.71,0:26:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your role has come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.55,0:26:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Secondary roles must leave the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.59,0:26:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.68,0:26:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Lets go.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.47,0:26:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't say goodbye,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.02,0:26:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because this house was destined for\Na goodbye from the very beginning!
